properties.text: Live Aid: Bob Geldof launched the world-wide concert to raise funds for the Ethiopian famine. The event was held in both London and Philadelphia and was watched by an estimated 1.9 billion in 160 countries.

The era of the yuppie saw Britons become bold and brash, and the UK flex its international muscle in the Falklands War. Britain celebrated two royal weddings, but also mourned terror attacks by the IRA and the Lockerbie bombing. As the mines were closed down traditional industries went into decline.

Royal Wedding: Prince Charles and Lady Diana Spencer married at St Paul's Cathedral in 1981. The British public enjoyed a national holiday to mark the occasion and more than 750 million people watched the ceremony.

Mobile phones: Once, when you wanted to call someone, you went home or to the nearest telephone box. But the 1980s saw the beginning of the rise of the mobile phone. Whilst the technology wasn't new, a brick-like phone became the accessory to show your wealth and power.
